WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-GB

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.666
How to select the Device Financing domain.

2
00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:06.830
If you selected the Device Financing domain during account creation, 

3
00:00:06.830 --> 00:00:10.999
your Knox Guard tenant includes a unique set of security-hardening mechanisms 

4
00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:13.333
and policies to protect your devices from hacking.

5
00:00:13.866 --> 00:00:17.412
These configurations, referred to as Hardened Security mode, 

6
00:00:17.413 --> 00:00:21.699
include several features that are automatically applied to your devices after activation.

7
00:00:22.266 --> 00:00:23.997
Key points to note:

8
00:00:23.998 --> 00:00:27.132
Hardened Security mode is mandatory for all new devices 

9
00:00:27.132 --> 00:00:29.432
when you select the device financing domain.

10
00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:33.163
Hardened Security mode is only available for devices that support 

11
00:00:33.163 --> 00:00:35.006
hardened security architecture.

12
00:00:35.007 --> 00:00:39.332
These includes Samsung Galaxy S26 and all subsequent models, 

13
00:00:39.333 --> 00:00:42.266
and the Galaxy A17 LTE.

14
00:00:42.266 --> 00:00:46.566
Once hardened security mode is applied, this setting cannot be reversed.

15
00:00:47.100 --> 00:00:51.266
Devices with hardened security mode are non-transferable to other domain types. 

16
00:00:51.266 --> 00:00:54.151
This means you cannot upload them to a different domain, 

17
00:00:54.152 --> 00:00:56.232
even if they are removed from Knox Guard. 

18
00:00:56.933 --> 00:01:00.699
You can review the list of Hardened Security mode features after selecting the 

19
00:01:00.699 --> 00:01:03.432
Device Financing domain during account creation.

20
00:01:03.900 --> 00:01:06.169
For more detailed descriptions of each feature, 

21
00:01:06.169 --> 00:01:09.466
refer to the Knox Guard admin guide, which is linked on the page.

22
00:01:10.300 --> 00:01:12.002
After reviewing the features, 

23
00:01:12.002 --> 00:01:14.633
you'll need to provide your company's contact information. 

24
00:01:15.333 --> 00:01:19.199
This information appears on the device screen during Knox Guard activation,

25
00:01:19.700 --> 00:01:24.100
and on the Customer Support screen whenever a device is in an Offline Lock state.

26
00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:27.407
Once you've entered your contact information, 

27
00:01:27.407 --> 00:01:30.769
confirm that you want to proceed with the device financing domain 

28
00:01:30.769 --> 00:01:34.165
and understand that Hardened Security mode will be applied to your devices.

29
00:01:34.966 --> 00:01:38.069
After a Samsung admin approves your Knox Guard account,

30
00:01:38.070 --> 00:01:41.620
your tenant will be registered in the device financing domain. 

31
00:01:41.621 --> 00:01:43.962
Your devices will then receive the added protection of 

32
00:01:43.963 --> 00:01:46.533
Hardened Security mode to safeguard them from hacking.

33
00:01:46.833 --> 00:01:49.261
For more information on Knox Guard domains, 

34
00:01:49.262 --> 00:01:54.866
check out our other videos in the series or visit our documentation at docs.samsungknox.com.

35
00:01:54.866 --> 00:01:56.266
Thanks for watching!

